This project, SliceSelect, uses the following third‑party libraries.
Each library is distributed under its own license, as noted below.
Please refer to the respective project pages for full license terms.

1) Flask

        Description: Web framework used to provide the HTTP API and web interface.

        Project URL: https://palletsprojects.com/p/flask/

        License: BSD‑3 (https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/stable/license/)

2) pydicom

        Description: Library for reading, modifying, and writing DICOM files.

        Project URL: https://pydicom.github.io/

        License: MIT (https://github.com/pydicom/dicom-database/blob/master/LICENSE)

3) Pillow

        Description: Python Imaging Library (PIL) fork used for image processing and PNG export.

        Project URL: https://python-pillow.org/

        License: Open Source MIT-CMU (https://github.com/python-pillow/Pillow/blob/main/LICENSE)

4) matplotlib

        Description: Plotting library used for image handling/visualization where applicable.

        Project URL: https://matplotlib.org/

        License: PSF‑style, BSD‑compatible open‑source license (https://matplotlib.org/stable/project/license.html)

5) NumPy

        Description: Fundamental package for numerical computing in Python.

        Project URL: https://numpy.org/

        License: NumPy (BSD‑style) license (https://numpy.org/doc/stable/license.html).

